You need to create a Recipe Webpage using only the following HTML tags:

Headings: <h1> to <h6>
Paragraph: <p>
Line break: <br>
Horizontal rule: <hr>
Text formatting: <strong>, <b>, <em>, <i>, <mark>
Lists: <ul>, <ol>, <li>
Requirements

Page Title: At the top of the page, display the recipe name using <h1>.
Introduction
Add a short description of the recipe inside a <p> tag.
Use <br> to show Prep Time and Cook Time on separate lines.
Ingredients Section
Add a section heading using <h2> called “Ingredients”.
List at least 5 ingredients using an unordered list (<ul>).
Use <mark> to highlight any optional ingredient.
Steps Section
Add a section heading using <h2> called “Steps”.
Write 4 or more steps in an ordered list (<ol>).
Use <em> and <strong> within steps to emphasize important actions.
Use <b> or <i> at least once to compare with <strong> and <em>.
Tips Section
Add a <h3> heading for “Tips”.
Write a small paragraph with at least one <i> and one <em> for emphasis.
Section Separation
Use <hr> to separate Ingredients, Steps, and Tips sections.
